\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The Application Preferences panel has several aspects that may be used to customise various parameters and operating characteristics of Calliope.  Application Preferences take effect on all documents in use.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The NeXTStep defaults database is used by Applications Preferences.  This provides a command-line interface to preferences. \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Other preferences pertain to documents on an individual basis and may have different values for different documents.  These are to be found in the Document Preferences Panel, which may be opened either with the \fs24\f1\b0\i0 D\f1 ocument\f2\f2 ®\f1\f1 P\f1 references\f0  menu command or by pressing the Document Preferences button on the Application Preferences Panel.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Colors\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The Colors aspect permits the user to specify the colours of both printing and non-printing features of the display.  The panel contains colour wells into which colours (see Tools\f2 ®\f0 Colors...) may be dragged.  \fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 ET\f0  must be pressed for the change to take effect.\par
