\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Background\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The colour of the background.  On a monochrome display, light grey is the default because experience shows that it is less of a strain on the eyes than is white, although some users will prefer to set the background colour to white because it resembles paper.  On a colour display it may be helpful to set the background to a very pale yellow, which is both restful to the eyes and offers good contrast with black.  The background colour is ignored when printing.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Invisible\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The colour in which invisible objects (see \b Visibility\b0 ) are displayed.  Invisible objects do not print on paper.  On a monochrome display, dark grey is the default.  On a colour display, a good choice is light blue, which is the traditional colour for copyeditor's pencil.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Markers\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The colour in which markers (such as the markers shown at the right-hand edge of each system) and margin lines are displayed.  Markers do not print on paper.  On a monochrome display, dark grey is the default.  On a colour display, a good choice is light blue for similar reasons as for invisible objects.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Selection\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The colour in which selected objects are displayed.  The selected system marker is also displayed in this colour.  On a monochrome display, the default is white, although if the user changes the background to white is it advisable to also change the selection colour.  On a colour display, red is a good choice.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Ink\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The colour in which printing graphics (all staff lines, musical objects, text, etc) is displayed and printed.  The obvious choice is black.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Tone 1\par
